    "oscillator_description": "The Sinusoid (Sine) oscillator is the core for phase modulation synthesis. It generates a pure sine wave with a 'Shape' parameter (28 variants including quadrant masking, phase shifts, and frequency-doubling). It features FM-style feedback (±400%) that feeds the output back into its own phase accumulator, with a 'Vintage FM' mode for smoother feedback. Other related sinusoid algorithms include FM2 and FM3 which provide integer-ratio FM/PM synthesis.",
